    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a lineup heavily leveraged toward speed and top-of-the-order run production. **Trea Turner** (79.76) stands as our premier play, benefiting from a soft matchup against Mart\u00edn P\u00e9rez. The combination of **Trea Turner** hitting leadoff and the favorable park environment against a mediocre starter creates an ideal environment for him to exploit the stolen base category. **Kyle Schwarber** (78.40) serves as the primary offensive anchor in that same contest, with his elite xwOBA (0.402) providing a massive floor for HR and RBI production. Meanwhile, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (74.17) remains a must-start despite an unfavorable batting order position; his matchup against Senga provides the perfect environment for his elite sprint speed to bridge the gap in our scarcest category, SB.\n\nThe decision to start **Hyeseong Kim** (70.52) over other middle infield options is driven by a massive +17% boost from a favorable matchup against Tomoyuki Sugano, suggesting he is primed to outperform his base projection. On the bench, **Victor Scott II** (48.83) was the toughest exclusion. While his elite speed remains a major draw for the Zebras, his projected role at the bottom of the order and the diminishing returns of a matchup against Peter Lambert tipped the scales in favor of **Caleb Durbin** (60.56), whose spot in the #2 hole against Casey Mize offers significantly higher run-scoring potential. \n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the lineup uncertainty; all scores are calculated on assumed batting orders. While **Yordan Alvarez** (68.39) and **Dillon Dingler** (55.25) provide strong upside, investors should note that **Dillon Dingler** is facing a tough southpaw in Ranger Suarez. Should any of these hitters shift downward in their respective lineups once official cards are posted, the optimizer may recalibrate their efficiency scores, potentially necessitating a move to the bench to preserve our game caps. **Zac Veen** remains a critical \"hold\" in the minors, and we continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, **Lars Nootbaar**, and **Luis Pena** as they work toward active roster availability.",
